   Descripción

   Learn the Secrets to helping other people by gaining a diploma in
   Counselling.
   Gain this qualification at Emagister.co.uk
   With our Counselling Diploma, you can become an agent of change and
   have a positive influence on the lives of many.
   Counselling has a massive impact on people’s lives, whether its
   marriage counselling, mental health counselling or rehabilitation
   counselling, it facilitates change and growth in people.
   Everyone can benefit hugely from working through their problems and
   concerns with a counsellor, who has the right approach and adequate
   knowledge to guide them to a happier life.
   To become a successful Counsellor, it is important to understand the
   history of counselling and psychotherapy, to understand the ethical and
   legal issued that surround it and to understand the various techniques
   that are used while counselling someone, matters which are all dealt
   with on this course.
   Counselling is an excellent career choice because of its high demand
   and the fact that you can carry it out from your own home, during the
   hours you prefer. In addition, you could go on to become a Clinical
   Psychologist, a Family Support Worker, a Life Coach or a Cognitive
   Behavioural Therapist, working either from home or within a
   professional setting.
   Start today at Emagister.co.uk with this Counselling Diploma.
   (BUTTON) Descripción completa Información importante
   ¿Qué objetivos tiene esta formación?

   Understanding the differences between the modes of complimentary
   therapy given to those interested in discussion therapy
   How to gather information and conduct research
   Develop efficient counselling abilities and learn how to interact
   effectively and professionally with outside organizations
   Discover ways to enhance effective communication with your client
   Learn to understand client preferences without engagement from others
   A great awareness of the dimensions of setting up a private business
   and how to achieve their duty as a counsellor
   How to properly facilitate and structure client appointments and
   facilitate reports as well as client progress
   ¿Esta formación es para mí?

   This qualification is designed for candidates who have already obtained
   a recognised qualification in counselling abilities and prefer to:
   Be prepared for work as a certified counsellor in a professional
   environment
   Learn more about counseling ethics, theory, and mental health
   Take the next stage in training to be a counsellor
   ¿Qué pasará tras pedir información?

   On receiving your request, one of our staff members will call you or
   send you a message by explaining everything about the course you are
   requesting information, including how you can sign up, payment options,
   exam, and enrollment requirements etc.

   Precio a usuarios Emagister: Special promotion price.

   Requisitos: This course is available to all students of all academic
   backgrounds, but a sound educational background would be an advantage
   Students must be ages 17 or above to join the qualification Plus, a
   basic understanding of the English language, ICT, numeracy, and
   literacy are essential to attend this course
